## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design a secure, cost-conscious AWS-native pipeline that handles PII responsibly using services like S3, Lambda, Comprehend, and DynamoDB, with proper error handling and auditing.

## Key Concepts
- PII detection: Amazon Comprehend PII entities
- Data flow: S3 -> Lambda -> S3 (redacted) -> DynamoDB
- Privacy controls: encryption at rest (SSE/KMS), data minimization
- Reliability: dead-letter queues (DLQ), retries, idempotent processing, logging

## Code Example
```javascript
const AWS = require('aws-sdk');
const s3 = new AWS.S3();
const comprehend = new AWS.Comprehend({region: 'us-east-1'});
async function redact(text) {
  const res = await comprehend.detectPiiEntities({ Text: text, LanguageCode: 'en' }).promise();
  let redacted = text;
  // naive approach: replace ranges from end to start to avoid offset shifts
  const ranges = res.Entities.map(e => ({ s: e.BeginOffset, e: e.EndOffset }));
  ranges.sort((a,b) => b.s - a.s);
  for (const r of ranges) {
    redacted = redacted.substring(0, r.s) + '[REDACTED]' + redacted.substring(r.e);
  }
  return redacted;
}
```

