## Why This Is Asked
Tests real-world orchestration across AWS AI services, privacy controls, and fault tolerance in a streaming-like ingest path. It probes trade-offs between latency, cost, and compliance when handling PII.

## Key Concepts
- Event-driven orchestration (S3 PUT, Lambda/EventBridge)
- Text analytics (Comprehend: intents, PII)
- Custom model inference (SageMaker endpoint)
- Data redaction and dual-storage (original + redacted) with KMS
- Upsert pattern in DynamoDB with IDs and metadata
- IAM, retries, observability, and cost controls

## Code Example
```javascript
// Minimal Node.js Lambda handler for the orchestrator
exports.handler = async (event) => {
  const record = event.Records[0];
  const bucket = record.s3.bucket.name;
  const key = record.s3.object.key;

  // 1. Fetch transcript from S3
  const transcript = await s3.getObject({ Bucket: bucket, Key: key }).promise();
  const chatData = JSON.parse(transcript.Body.toString());

  // 2. Extract text for analysis
  const chatText = chatData.messages.map(m => m.content).join(' ');

  // 3. Comprehend analysis
  const [comprehendResult, piiResult] = await Promise.all([
    comprehend.detectDominantLanguage({ Text: chatText }).promise(),
    comprehend.detectPiiEntities({ Text: chatText, LanguageCode: 'en' }).promise()
  ]);

  // 4. SageMaker risk classification
  const riskResponse = await sageMakerRuntime.invokeEndpoint({
    EndpointName: process.env.RISK_ENDPOINT,
    ContentType: 'application/json',
    Body: JSON.stringify({ text: chatText, metadata: chatData.metadata })
  }).promise();

  const riskClassification = JSON.parse(riskResponse.Body.toString());

  // 5. Redact PII and store both versions
  const redactedText = await redactPii(chatText, piiResult.Entities);
  const [originalKey, redactedKey] = await Promise.all([
    storeTranscript(chatData, 'original'),
    storeTranscript({...chatData, text: redactedText}, 'redacted')
  ]);

  // 6. Upsert DynamoDB item
  await dynamodb.putItem({
    TableName: process.env.CHAT_TABLE,
    Item: {
      chatId: chatData.id,
      userHash: chatData.userId,
      language: comprehendResult.Languages[0].LanguageCode,
      riskScore: riskClassification.score,
      originalKey,
      redactedKey,
      detectedIntents: comprehendResult.Intents
    }
  }).promise();
};
```

