## Code Example

```javascript
exports.handler = async (event) => {
  // 1. Get S3 object
  const s3Object = await s3.getObject({
    Bucket: event.bucket,
    Key: event.key
  }).promise();

  const ticket = JSON.parse(s3Object.Body);

  // 2. Validate schema
  if (!ticket.ticketId || !ticket.text) {
    throw new Error('Invalid ticket schema');
  }

  // 3. Classify with Comprehend
  const classifyResult = await comprehend.classifyDocument({
    Text: ticket.text,
    EndpointArn: COMPREHEND_ENDPOINT
  }).promise();

  // 4. Extract entities
  const entitiesResult = await comprehend.detectEntities({
    Text: ticket.text,
    LanguageCode: 'en'
  }).promise();

  const topEntities = entitiesResult.Entities
    .sort((a, b) => b.Score - a.Score)
    .slice(0, 3);

  // 5. Store results in S3 (encrypted)
  const output = {
    ticketId: ticket.ticketId,
    category: classifyResult.Classes[0].Name,
    confidence: classifyResult.Classes[0].Score,
    entities: topEntities,
    timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
  };

  await s3.putObject({
    Bucket: OUTPUT_BUCKET,
    Key: `results/${ticket.ticketId}.json`,
    Body: JSON.stringify(output),
    ServerSideEncryption: 'aws:kms'
  }).promise();

  // 6. Upsert DynamoDB
  await dynamoDB.put({
    TableName: TICKETS_TABLE,
    Item: {
      ticketId: ticket.ticketId,
      s3Key: `results/${ticket.ticketId}.json`,
      category: output.category,
      confidence: output.confidence,
      entities: topEntities
    }
  }).promise();

  return { statusCode: 200, body: 'Success' };
};
```

## Architecture Considerations

| Component | Consideration |
|-----------|----------------|
| **S3 Trigger** | Use S3 Event Notifications to trigger Lambda on object creation |
| **Lambda** | Configure timeout (30s+), memory (512MB+), and VPC if needed |
| **IAM** | Least privilege: Lambda needs read on input bucket, write on output bucket, Comprehend and DynamoDB access |
| **Encryption** | Use SSE-KMS for S3 buckets; enable at-rest encryption for DynamoDB |
| **Error Handling** | Implement DLQ for failed processing; add try-catch with exponential backoff for API calls |
| **Cost** | Comprehend pricing is per request; consider batching if high volume |
| **Privacy** | Never log PII; use AWS PrivateLink for Comprehend if required |

